## üîß Troubleshooting & Pro Tips

### Common Issues & Solutions

**Problem 1: "Canvas content sounds generic/bland"**  
**Solution:** You're not providing enough specific constraints. Add: (1) Your brand voice examples, (2) Specific phrases you use, (3) Things to avoid, (4) Unique perspective or thesis. Generic input = generic output.

**Problem 2: "AI keeps going off-topic in long articles"**  
**Solution:** Work section-by-section in Canvas, not "write the whole thing." After each section, review and refine before generating next. This maintains coherence and focus.

**Problem 3: "Factual errors or outdated information"**  
**Solution:** Use GPT-5's web browsing mode for research-heavy content. Say: "Search for current statistics on [X] from 2024-2025" before writing. Always fact-check claims.

**Problem 4: "Content lacks my personality"**  
**Solution:** Feed GPT-5 5-10 examples of your best writing and say: "Write in this same voice." Be specific: "I use short sentences. I avoid corporate jargon. I tell stories. I end paragraphs with one-line zingers."

**Problem 5: "Struggling to maintain consistency across team"**  
**Solution:** Create brand voice document with 10+ examples of good writing + style guidelines. Require team to include this in every prompt. Use same templates.

