### Pro Tips from Experts

**üí° Power Technique 1: "Two-Pass Writing"**  
First pass: Generate fast, imperfect draft covering all points. Second pass: Use Canvas to refine each section for tone, clarity, and depth. Separate creation from editing = better final product.

**üí° Power Technique 2: "Voice Calibration Library"**  
Maintain a doc with 15-20 of your best writing pieces. When starting any project, show GPT-5 3-5 relevant examples. "Write like these examples" is more powerful than describing your voice.

**üí° Power Technique 3: "Headline Multiplication"**  
For any article, generate 20 headline options with different angles (curiosity, benefit, how-to, contrarian, data-driven). Pick best 3, test with colleagues, choose winner.

**üí° Power Technique 4: "Research-First Writing"**  
For complex topics: (1) Have GPT-5 research and synthesize 10 sources, (2) Review synthesis and add your perspective, (3) Then generate article. Results in much deeper content.

**üí° Power Technique 5: "Content Atomization"**  
Every long-form piece should generate 15-20 micro-assets. Use Template 2 systematically. Never publish just one format when you can publish 15.

